-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/85b06/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 256w,\n/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/bc282/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 512w,\n/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/f1720/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcSet=\"/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/85b06/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 256w,\n/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/bc282/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 512w,\n/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/f1720/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 1024w\" src=\"/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/f1720/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png\" alt=\"An image of three young girls smiling and playing outside\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/85b06/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 256w,\n/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/bc282/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 512w,\n/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/f1720/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/85b06/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 256w,\n/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/bc282/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 512w,\n/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/f1720/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 1024w\" src=\"/static/4785f94f3e5cf99587c66a17aae2d523/f1720/1_Image-SJRC-1024x538.png\" alt=\"An image of three young girls smiling and playing outside\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sunday, July 11<sup>th</sup>, in the San Antonio Express-News we were able to feature the organization, <a href=\"https://sjrctexas.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>SJRC</strong></a>, in our latest edition of <a href=\"https://thepmgrp.com/agency-news/the-pm-group-and-express-news-launch-a-new-feature-on-nonprofits-making-a-difference-in-san-antonio/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Making a Difference in San Antonio</strong></a>. SJRC has spent over 37 years caring for families and children most affected by trauma, abuse, and neglect. Although originally tied to a Nevada child welfare organization, for the last five years SJRC has been focused on caring for Texas kids. It was important for their team to serve the local community as they are based out of Bulverde, Texas and know just how many children and families need support.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The organization offers foster care and adoption services for local foster homes as well as residential foster care. They also provide resources and housing for pregnant and parenting teens, a prevention program, and resources and housing for survivors of child sex trafficking. Being a safe haven for 250 kids every day takes resources and time and as they continue to grow in the number of individuals they can help, they continue to call on the support of the community.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can read the full article on <a href=\"http://www.mysanantonio.com/sponsoredarticles/article/Making-a-Difference-in-San-Antonio-SJRC-Texas-16305007.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>MYSA</strong></a> and visit their website to learn more and donate</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://thepmgrp.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>About The PM Group</strong></a>: The PM Group was founded in 1988. For over 33 years, the agency has continued to grow and is San Antonio’s largest advertising agency. The PM Group’s client roster spans numerous industries including home services, automotive, CPG, entertainment and sports marketing, legal, business services, non-profits, real estate and fitness. For two consecutive years now, the Agency has set annual revenue records with the addition of six new clients and through the continued success of our existing clients. Additionally, the agency hosts their annual Charity Gala that to date has raised millions of dollars for local San Antonio area non-profit organizations in the last 15 years! In 2020 alone, the Agency donated over $1,050,000 to local non-profits. It is our way of giving back to the community that we so humbly serve.</p>\n","title":"Making a Difference in San Antonio: SJRC","seo":{"breadcrumbs":[{"text":"Making a Difference in San Antonio: SJRC","url":"/making-a-difference-in-san-antonio-sjrc/"}],"title":"Making a Difference in San Antonio: SJRC | The PM Group","metaDesc":"The PM Group features SJRC in latest edition of Making a Difference in San Antonio in the San Antonio Express-News.","focuskw":"SJRC","metaKeywords":"","metaRobotsNoindex":"index","metaRobotsNofollow":"follow","opengraphTitle":"Making a Difference in San Antonio: SJRC | The PM Group","opengraphDescription":"The PM Group features SJRC in latest edition of Making a Difference in San Antonio in the San Antonio Express-News.","opengraphImage":{"altText":"An image of three young girls smiling and playing outside","sourceUrl":"https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Image-SJRC.png","srcSet":"https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Image-SJRC-300x158.png 300w, https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Image-SJRC-1024x538.png 1024w, https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Image-SJRC-768x403.png 768w, https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Image-SJRC.png 1200